			<div class="grid__item lap-and-up-one-third">
				<div class="top-pull">
					<div class="padded-block bg-purple">
						<h1>Careers Mentoring</h1>

						<div class="intro">
							<p>If you want to share your time and experience with current students or fellow Orielenses, there are a variety of options offered by Oriel and the University</p>

													</div>
					</div>

											<div class="padded-block bg-green">
							
							<ul class="anchor-nav">
															<li><a href="#mentoring">The University Careers Service</a></li>
															<li><a href="#">Oxford Alumni Community</a></li>
														</ul>
						</div>
					
					<img src="" class="side-image">
				</div>
			</div><div class="grid__item lap-and-up-two-thirds">
				<div class="content-block">
					<h2></h2>

											<div class="content-section" id="mentoring">
							<h3>The University Careers Service</h3>
							<p>If you would be happy for students or other alumni to contact you for careers advice, you can register yourself as a mentor on the University Careers Service <a href="http://www.careers.ox.ac.uk/our-services/careerconnect/" target="_blank">website</a>. Just click on the &#8216;Alumni Mentors&#8217; button and follow the instructions.</p>
<p>Oxford students and alumni interested in a career in your field will then be able to contact you, and you can specify what you would be able to do to help themÂ &#8211; for example, if you&#8217;d be able to offer an internship or have an informal chat.</p>
						</div>
											<div class="content-section" id="">
							<h3>Oxford Alumni Community</h3>
							<p><a href="https://oxfordalumnicommunity.org/" target="_blank">The Oxford Alumni Community</a> also offers a mentoring scheme. The site allows you to create a profile, connect it to your LinkedIn or Facebook, and then find other Oxford alumni who might be interested in your career path. You can volunteer to be a &#8216;Mentor&#8217;, or you can request to be someone else&#8217;s &#8216;Mentee&#8217;.</p>
						</div>
									</div>
			</div>
			<div class="grid__item"><div class="lion"></div></div>
		</div>
	</div>
</div>


